Federal Reserve Begins Sales of TIPS Under Operation Twist

-- B y   L i z   M c C o r m i c k
-- 
2011-10-17T14:15:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/federal-reserve-begins-sales-of-tips-under-operation-twist.html
The  Federal Reserve  began selling as
much of $1.5 billion of Treasury Inflation Protected Securities
as part of its program to replace $400 billion of short-term
debt in its portfolio with longer-term Treasuries in an effort
to reduce borrowing costs.  The central bank is offering securities maturing from April
2012 to July 2014 for sale between 10:15 a.m. and 11 a.m. New
York time, according to a Federal Reserve Bank of New York
statement  today .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Liz McCormick in New York at 
 emccormick7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dave Liedtka at 
 dliedtka@bloomberg.net  